com.bmd.android.collection.filter

Interface AdvancedFilter<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the element type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Filter<E>

    public interface AdvancedFilter<E>
extends Filter<E>
    This interface defines an advanced element filter.

    An advanced filter may retain an internal state which must be reset each time the initialize(FilterIterator) method is call.

    Created by davide on 3/14/14.

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        void initialize(AdvancedFilter.FilterIterator<E> iterator)
        This method is called each time the filter needs to be initialized with the iterator resulting from the application of previous filter to the sparse collection iterable.

        The specific implementation may use the passed iterator to analyze the elements before the application of the filter itself.

        Parameters:
        iterator - the filtered iterator.
